artery","Inferior mesenteric artery","Lumbar arteries"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior mesenteric artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer as it is the primary blood supply for the midgut. This includes structures such as the ascending colon, appendix, and jejunum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect as none of them supply the midgut and instead supply various other structures, as listed:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior phrenic artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the diaphragm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecoeliac trunk\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the foregut, including the lower oesophagus, stomach, proximal duodenum, liver, gallbladder, and pancreas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior mesenteric artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the hindgut.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elumbar arteries\u003C/strong\u003E supply the posterior abdominal wall and spinal cord.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the blood supply of different regions of the gastrointestinal tract is of high value in understanding various pathological conditions and surgical procedures involving these areas, such as those in gastrointestinal surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The superior mesenteric artery supplies the midgut structures including the distal duodenum, jejunum, ileum, ascending colon and proximal 2/3 of transverse colon.","The coeliac trunk supplies foregut structures while the inferior mesenteric artery supplies hindgut structures.","The embryological development of the gut determines its blood supply, with each portion receiving blood from specific vessels."],"references":["Netter, F. H. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: Classic Regional Approach-Ebook. 2022. Elsevier Health Sciences","Shahoud JS, Miao JH, Bolla SR. Anatomy, Thorax, Heart Aorta. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538140/Shaikh H, Wehrle CJ, Khorasani-Zadeh A. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Superior Mesenteric Artery. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519560/","Jacob, S. (2007). Human anatomy: a clinically-orientated approach. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48966"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14521"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48966","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48966"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-21T10:47:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-21T10:48:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7216"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63512"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Le